A flame jet burst from Thassalin's jaws as the colossal Thraki set a precise portion of the forest ablaze, then circled overhead, observing it for a while. Strangely, as it had slowed down, the weird cries behind him had stopped. Thassalin had forgotten that he had passengers on his back.
"Come on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thraki before!"
"My flight is very different. I am not lifted abruptly by a huge pink dragon!"
"It's not so unpleasant, is it, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly did not agree with Nyssi; he seemed less black than usual and had dug his claws into Thassalin's back, causing the Thraki to bleed, but obviously, he didn't care much about that. Still, Thassalin realized he had terrified his new friends and found a clearing to land.
"MY APOLOGIES, I SMELLED SOMETHING. IT WAS NECESSARY FOR ME TO CHECK."
"Were you forced to drag us here with you?"
"He will find a way,"
"Agreed, but does Retvik know how to drive?"
Nissy blinked and turned towards Tenuk. "Of course he knows how to drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik driving a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I've never seen him drive Kayel's cute little car either, and if he started coming to work by car, it's only because YOU bring us. He just has this bike."
A burst of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin was suddenly hysterical, and no one could figure out what made him laugh. It took him a bit too long to regain his composure.
"I'M SORRY, BUT I IMAGINED YOUR BIG FRIEND IN ARMOR ON A MINISCULE BICYCLE MEANT FOR CHILDREN. IT WAS SO HILARIOUS! IF ONLY I HAD TELEPATHY. THAT'S A VALUABLE THOUGHT! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what Thassalin was thinking. "Yes, that's right. But what did you pick up and why did you fly off so quickly?"
Thassalin grumbled, took off, and briefly disappeared before returning and dropping a carcass in front of Nyssi. It was an Orothrack, a very rare golden and white dragon-like creature. But it was missing its head. "ANOTHER KILL. I HEAR THEIR CRIES. I SENSE THEIR BLOOD. I'M PROGRAMMED TO PROTECT AND PURSUE. AS YISINI DEMANDS. THE CREATURES ARE CLOSE."
The powerful Thraki suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also stopped, their attention drawn by a gap in the clearing. Something large and black was staring at them, hissing. Whatever it was, this thing spread two colossal sets of wings and charged straight at Thassalin, paying no mind to the three smaller beings in its path. Kayel and Tenuk managed to take cover barely in time, but Nyssi found herself dragged and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin responded to the aggression by grabbing Nyssi and sending her flying onto his back using his incredibly long and agile tail, before taking off. The two-winged black creature quickly rushed after them in pursuit.
Kayel exhaled as he drew the rifle from his back, then opened a pouch containing a belt of ammunition. He slung it over his shoulder for easy access, but soon realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were no longer visible.
"Hey Tenuk, would you like to turn into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"You want to chase them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... one of them is a giant monster!"
"And so what? I have an ultra powerful rifle in my hands right now, ready to serve. All I need to do is see it to shoot at it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to give himself some space. With a faint grumble slightly pained, his body unfolded, his fur was replaced by scales, and his arms transformed into wings. He quickly reverted to the usual light blue Thraki, but his eyes remained red.
"Climb."
Having restored Thraki to a more normal appearance, Tenuk now had a back covered in scaly plates, but a pair of spikes had also grown on him, practical for Kayel to grab onto. Tenuk needed a bit of time to take off, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to pursue.
However, Tenuk and Kayel realized quickly that they were not alone. A second dark creature emerged from below, and Tenuk managed to avoid it at the last moment.
I suppose this is the other scary big monster that was worrying Lanex? Kayel frowned as he tried to aim at the second beast, missed his target, and quickly reloaded his weapon.
Tenuk did not react. He was too focused on flying towards Nyssi and Thassalin, despite the other creature pursuing them. Kayel clumsily spun around himself, facing the monster. The fact that it was pursuing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it made it easier for him to aim and shoot. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature, which let out a cry of pain before disappearing again under the trees. Kayel did not know if she was still following them, but she certainly would not be able to catch up with them.
Farther away, Nyssi desperately clung on, while Thassalin flew in circles, shooting bursts of flames at the blackened monster. Although the creature was clearly wounded, it seemed furious and determined to fight, and the fireballs did not seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin straightened up, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her weapon, a reliable rifle. Of course, it was not meant for such situations, but a volley of shots would surely at least dissuade the black beast, right?
